review_blob: Much better than the Leffe Ruby I had a few minutes earlier, so perhaps Im ranking this beer better than it deserves. Tastes like cherry juice mixed with a bit of beer. Overall, drinkable, but nothing special.
Smells and looks great. Nice pinkish head. Terrible taste which is difficult to pin point. Feels like too many ingredients that dont fit together. I couldnt finish drinking it, which is rare.

330cc bottle poured (gushing) into glass. Color is dark brown with a lot of sediment. The off white head is initially large but doesnt stay for long. Full body, medium-high carbonation. Sweet malty taste with caramel and ripe fruit aroma. Low bitterness. High ABV is very obvious. Excellent beer.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: 0.5L bottle poured into glass. Very hazy amber color, with small off white head that doesnt stay for long. Full body, medium-high carbonation. Strong aroma of wheat and hops. Slightly sweet. Medium bitterness. High ABV is very obvious. Overall very nice and flavorful beer.

355cc bottle poured into glass. Hazy dark amber color, with small off white light brown head that doesnt stay for long. Full body, medium-high carbonation. Sweet malty taste. Medium bitterness. High ABV is very obvious. Overall quite nice, but not amazing.

Can of Quollfrisch Premium Lager poured into plastic glass. Medium carbonation, low body, 
Medium bitterness, clear yellow color, white and relatively stable head. Typical macro pale lager. Drinkable but watery and boring.

355cc bottle poured into glass. Very dark red color, with light brown head that doesnt stay for long. Medium body, high carbonation (a bit too high for my liking). Aroma of malt and citrus. Low bitterness. Nice beer.
0.33L bottle poured into glass. Hazy amber color. Small white head. Medium body. Carbonation is a bit too high for my liking. Tastes like wheat beer. Pretty nice overall.
beer_name: HaDubim Brewers Choice Rye Saison Beer

review_blob: 0.5L bottle poured into glass. Clear amber color, with a nice but fast to dissipate head. Medium bitterness, body and carbonation. Aroma of bread and caramel. Boring but drinkable beer.

0.35L bottle, poured into glass. Strong malt aroma with hints of caramel, bread and chocolate. Low bitterness. Sweet. Full bodied. Dark brown head is foamy and dissipates quickly. Super delicious beer.

0.5L bottle, brewed in CZ, poured into glass. Off white head, fast to dissipate. Color is very dark red. Clear and sparkling. Strong malt aroma, with caramel and chocolate hints. Very little hops. Almost no bitterness. Light sweetness, medium body. Average carbonation. Overall - unsophisticated, but very enjoyable beer; better than most common macro lagers (which granted are of the pale variety).
0.33 L bottle poured into glass. Thick white head. Hazy light amber color. Aroma of citrus and hops. Low bitterness, medium sweetness. Medium body and carbonation. Overall good beer.

0.5 L bottle (brewed in England), poured into glass. Aroma of cereal and bread. Hazy dark amber color, head is white and dissipates quickly. Medium bitterness. Medium-light body, low carbonation. Drinkable but boring.
UPDATED: JAN 15, 2015

Bottle brewed in Belgium and poured into glass. Head is off white and fast to dissipate. Color is dark reddish brown. Very hazy. Average body and medium carbonation. Aroma is malty. Quite sweet. Very tasty and enjoyable beer.

Bottle brewed in England and poured into glass. Head is off white and is relatively thin. Color is dark (but very clear) reddish brown. Average body and carbonation. Aroma is malty. Slightly more bitter than average, with a hint of sweetness. Good beer, but not as exceptional as I had expected.

330cc bottle. Dark muddy brown color. Medium-high carbonation. Head is off white and not very stable. Aroma of malt, vanilla, citrus and yeast. Taste is sweet with low bitterness. Overall - much better than it looks.
Bottle. Dark reddish brown color. Off white head. Medium body. Malty aroma with sweet caramel notes. Very tasty and enjoyable beer.

Bottle, brewed in Belgium. Light amber color. A bit hazy. Head is light colored and fast to dissipate. Somewhat over-carbonated for my liking. Light body. Yeasty aroma. Light sourness. OK beer, but nothing amazing.

Aroma of malt, citrus and hops. Amber color, off white head that doesnt last long (some spots of foam do remain), a bit hazy. Medium bitterness. Body is relatively light, more fizzy than usual. Overall a very nice ale.
Very nice pale lager. Amber colored, stable head, medium body. Light sweetness with medium bitterness. Tasty and enjoyable beer.
Chinese brewed 330cc bottle. Nice golden color, though head was minimal and fast to dissipate. Hardly any flavor, aroma or body. Very easy to drink.
UPDATED: SEP 11, 2013
